</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bluclin71335.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kaladur>Kaladur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/17/01 1:57:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=603.topic&index=84>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> FFA</span><hr size=1> Assuming all guilds involved were powerful enough to do Trak or VS on a moment's notice (and assuming there weren't too many of them), FFA would work better, but on Luclin, we have guilds that need almost every member present to kill even Kelorek'Dar. They still should have the right to try!<br>
<br>
We have lots of guilds that need to multi-guild to even have a _chance_ at taking out Trak. They still should have the right to try! But they can't do this on a moment's notice. Furthermore, there are less options for them if what they want to do is taken. <br>
<br>
So try to understand the point of view of these guilds.<br>
<br>
With any guild that's majority 56+, you _CAN_ just move to a different spawn/zone. Kael camped? Let's kill Lord Velketor. Velketor not up? Let's kill Severilous or Wuoshi or hit Siren's grotto or Necropolis or Icewell Keep or VS or Trak or any number of other raid spots.<br>
<br>
This works fine for about 3 or 4 guilds on the server.<br>
<br>
The other 20+ high level guilds can't do this.<br>
<br>
Which means, they can't _just_ go somewhere else. The ONLY way they can ever have a shot at taking down some of these ubermobs is lots of planning, a calendar, and the understanding that some other guild isn't going to run over them.<br>
<br>
What has to be decided is this: How do we give everyone a fair shot?<br>
<br>
If you can kill three dragons in one day, more power to you... _assuming_ that someone else didn't have one of them reserved. How many guilds can say &quot;Venril Sathir is up! Everyone head to Karnor ASAP.&quot; and kill him? Not many. <br>
<br>
And yet the other guilds deserve a chance to kill him. Without the calendar, the other guilds _will_ get stepped on.<br>
<br>
So, while I feel FFA seems to be working fine for LoS and Apex and a few others with respect to each other, it's only because we DO have the option of going somewhere else. <br>
<br>
I guarantee you there's somewhere Apex can go raid, any time of the week, that's not camped. In fact, there's probably 5 or 6 raids we could do without prior notice and not have to worry about the calendar or even running into anyone in the same zone.<br>
<br>
That's a luxury, fyi, of being on a relatively younger server.  <br>
<br>
This won't last forever! And along the way, growing pains will occur, as more and more guilds get powerful enough to start trying mobs that the top guilds can do whenever they want.<br>
<br>
So for the moment I suggest the following: Those who have the option of going wherever the hell they want will continue to do so. To be fair to those guilds who CAN'T do this, please please follow the calendar if someone's reserved something.<br>
<br>
Eventually, we won't just be able to kill Wuoshi whenever we want. There'll be enough guilds that can handle dragons that we'll start seeing every dragon reserved on the calendar all the time.<br>
<br>
This will cause the guilds who have been used to having free reign some consternation, but they must accept it, and play fair with the up-and-comers. Nobody owns this server, and anyone who thinks that &quot;might makes right&quot; and &quot;survival of the fittest&quot; is how you want this server to get, please go somewhere else where it's already like that and let the rest of us try to live in some kind of harmony.<br>
